{
  "text": "Sarcomatous components of germ-cell tumours, especially rhabdomyosarcoma, have a proper metastatic potential and a poor prognosis, particularly in adults and if the primary site is mediastinal [CITATION_1] . This prognosis can be influenced by many factors such as resectability of the tumour and histopathological subtype of the malignant component, its occurrence in a metastatic site and its sensitivity to chemotherapy [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
